WQ4

Molly Wilson

2022-09-14

samples <- read_excel(here("water_quality", "data", "samples.xlsx"), sheet = "raw_data") %>%  
  clean_names() %>%
  filter(id != c("E1", "E2")) %>%
  select(-nitrate_raw, -phosphate_raw) %>%
  mutate(date = as.character(date),
         month = month(ymd(date), label = TRUE),
         year = year(ymd(date)),
         date_label = paste(as.character(month), as.character(year)),
         salinity = salinity/1000, # ppm -> ppt
         tds = tds/1000, # ppm -> ppt
         enterococci = as.numeric(replace(enterococci, enterococci == "ND", 0)),
         row = row_number()) %>%
  left_join(read_excel(here("water_quality", "data", "samples.xlsx"), sheet = "sites") %>%
  clean_names(), by = "id") %>%
  unite(id_site, id, site, sep = " (", remove = F) %>%
  mutate(id_site = paste0(id_site, ")"),
         date_cat = case_when(date == "2022-09-06" ~ "September 2022",
                              date %in% c("2021-08-11") ~ "Summer samples",
                              date %in% c("2021-04-06", "2022-04-07") ~ "Winter samples"),
         date_cat2 = if_else(date == "2022-09-06", "September 2022", "Previous samples"))
# Target ranges
rect_dat_ph = data.frame(xmin = -Inf, xmax = Inf, ymin = 7.7, ymax = 8.5) # 7.7 and 8.5 units  (EPMA, 2019)
rect_dat_sal = data.frame(xmin = -Inf, xmax = Inf, ymin = 32, ymax = 42) # 32,000 to 42,000 ppm (NOAA)
rect_dat_do = data.frame(xmin = -Inf, xmax = Inf, ymin = 6, ymax = Inf) # Must be greater than 6.0 ppm  (EPMA, 2019)
rect_dat_temp = data.frame(xmin = -Inf, xmax = Inf, ymin = 23, ymax = 29.6) # 2329.6Celsius (NOAA)
rect_dat_ent = data.frame(xmin = -Inf, xmax = Inf, ymin = 0, ymax = 33) # (below 33, EPMA)

c_range <- "slategray1" # setting color for target range in graphs

WQ1-WQ4 trends

shapes_dates <- c(16, 1, 2)
colors_dates <- c("blue", "black", "black")
alphas_dates <- c(1, 0.3, 0.3)
theme <- theme_bw() +
  theme(legend.text = element_text(size = 9), 
        legend.title = element_text(size = 10))

# pH: 7.7 and 8.5 units  (EPMA, 2019)
ph <- ggplot() +
  geom_rect(data = rect_dat_ph, 
              aes(xmin = xmin, xmax = xmax, ymin = ymin, ymax = ymax, fill = "What"),
              alpha = 0.4) +
  scale_fill_manual(values = c_range, guide = "none") +
  geom_point(data = filter(samples, !str_detect(id, "^S")), aes(x = id, y = ph, alpha = date_cat, shape = date_cat, color = date_cat)) +
  scale_shape_manual(name = "", values = shapes_dates) +
  scale_color_manual(name = "", values = colors_dates) +
  scale_alpha_manual(name = "", values = alphas_dates) +
  labs(x = "", y = "pH") +
  ylim(5, 9) +
  theme

# TDS
tds <- ggplot() +
  geom_point(data = filter(samples, !str_detect(id, "^S")), aes(x = id, y = tds, shape = date_cat, alpha = date_cat, color = date_cat)) +
  scale_shape_manual(name = "", values = shapes_dates) +
  scale_color_manual(name = "", values = colors_dates) +
  scale_alpha_manual(name = "", values = alphas_dates) +
  labs(x = "", y = "TDS") +
  ylim(30, 60) +
  theme
ggsave(here("water_quality", "figs", "WQ4", "tds.png"), width = 6, height = 4)

Means and SE

summary <- samples %>%
  filter(!str_detect(id, "^S")) %>%
  select(-c(id, type, site, month, year, row, date_label, date_cat, date_cat2)) %>%
  mutate(enterococci = as.numeric(enterococci)) %>%
  pivot_longer(-c(id_site, date), names_to = "metric", values_to = "value") %>%
  group_by(metric, date) %>%
  summarise(n = n(),
            mean = mean(value),
            sd = sd(value),
            se = sd/sqrt(n))

Sargassum

sarg_colors <- c("firebrick3", "darkorange2", "goldenrod1", "slategray3", "cyan4")
sargassum <- samples %>%
  filter(date == "2022-09-06" & str_detect(id, "^S|^C|^N")) %>%
  mutate(category = case_when(id %in% c("C1", "C2") ~ "Controls",
                              id %in% c("N1", "N2") ~ "Nurseries",
                              id %in% c("S1", "S4") ~ "Mat center",
                              id %in% c("S2", "S5") ~ "Mat edge",
                              id %in% c("S3", "S6") ~ "200m from edge")) %>%
  mutate(id = factor(id, levels = c("S1", "S4", "S2", "S5", "S3", "S6", "C1", "C2", "N1", "N2"))) %>%
  mutate(category = factor(category, levels = c("Mat center", "Mat edge", "200m from edge", "Controls", "Nurseries")))
theme <- theme_bw() +
  theme(legend.text = element_text(size = 11), 
        legend.title = element_text(size = 12))

# pH:
ph <- ggplot() +
  geom_rect(data = rect_dat_ph, 
              aes(xmin = xmin, xmax = xmax, ymin = ymin, ymax = ymax, fill = "What"),
              alpha = 0.3) +
  scale_fill_manual(values = c_range, guide = "none") +
  geom_point(data = sargassum, aes(x = id, y = ph, color = category, group = category), size = 3) +
  labs(x = "", y = "pH") +
  scale_color_manual(values = sarg_colors, name = "") +
  ylim(5, 9) +
  theme

# TDS
tds <- ggplot() +
  geom_point(data = sargassum, aes(x = id, y = tds, color = category, group = category), size = 3) +
  scale_color_manual(values = sarg_colors, name = "") +
  labs(x = "", y = "TDS") +
  ylim(30, 60) +
  theme

              aes(xmin = xmin, xmax = xmax, ymin = ymin, ymax = ymax, fill = "What"),
              alpha = 0.3) +
  scale_fill_manual(values = c_range, guide = "none") +
  geom_point(data = sargassum, aes(x = id, y = temperature, color = category, group = category), size = 3) +
  scale_color_manual(values = sarg_colors, name = "") +
  labs(x = "", y = expression("Temperature ("*~degree*C*")")) +
  ylim(18, 32) +
  theme

# Conductivity (no reference)
conductivity <- ggplot() +
  geom_point(data = sargassum, aes(x = id, y = conductivity, color = category, group = category), size = 3) +
  scale_color_manual(values = sarg_colors, name = "") +
  labs(x = "", y = expression("Conductivity ("*mu*S*" "*cm^-1*")")) +
  ylim(30000, 60000) +
  theme

# Enterococci
enterococci <- ggplot() +
  geom_rect(data = rect_dat_ent, 
              aes(xmin = xmin, xmax = xmax, ymin = ymin, ymax = ymax, fill = "What"),
              alpha = 0.3) +
  scale_fill_manual(values = c_range, guide = "none") +
  geom_point(data = sargassum, aes(x = id, y = enterococci, color = category, group = category), size = 3) +
  scale_color_manual(values = sarg_colors, name = "") +
  labs(x = "", y = expression("Enterococci (cfu 100"*ml^-1*")")) +
  ylim(0, 35) +
  theme
ggarrange(ph, do, tds, turbidity, nitrates, phosphates, temperature, enterococci, salinity, conductivity, 
          ncol = 2, nrow = 5, common.legend = TRUE, legend = "top")
